Package jetbrains.exodus.entitystore

Interface Entity

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Entity>
    public interface Entity
extends java.lang.Comparable<Entity>
    Entity is an object in the EntityStore. Any Entity has type and unique id. Entity can have properties and blobs, and can be linked. Each property, blob or link is identified by its name. Although entity properties are expected to be Comparable, only Java primitives types, Strings and ComparableSet values can be used by default. Use registerCustomPropertyType() to define your own property type.

    To create new entity, use StoreTransaction.newEntity(String): 

         final Entity user = txn.newEntity("User");
    To get unique if of and entity, use getId(): 
         final EntityId id = user.getId();
    To get existing entity by id, use StoreTransaction.getEntity(EntityId): 
         final Entity user = txn.getEntity(id);
    See Also:
    EntityStore, EntityId, StoreTransaction

      • setBlob

        void setBlob​(@NotNull
             @NotNull java.lang.String blobName,
             @NotNull
             @NotNull java.io.File file)
        Sets value (as contents of File) of blob with specified name. It is preferred to use files which located on the same disk partition as the blob vault itself, otherwise transaction can take long amount of time because file will be copied into the another disk partition. In the last case better to use setBlob(String, InputStream) instead, because data will be copied first into the temporary location inside of blob vault.
        Parameters:
        blobName - name of the blob
        file - blob value as InputStream
        See Also:
        getBlob(String), getBlobSize(String), getBlobString(String), setBlob(String, File), setBlobString(String, String), deleteBlob(String), PersistentEntityStoreConfig.getMaxInPlaceBlobSize(), PersistentEntityStoreConfig.getBlobsDirectoryLocation()

      • setLink

        boolean setLink​(@NotNull
                @NotNull java.lang.String linkName,
                @Nullable
                @Nullable Entity target)
        Links this entity with target one by link with specified name. Unlike addLink(String, Entity), the method doesn't add new target if any with the same link already exists, but overrides the old target. So there can be only 0 or 1 link with specified name set by this method.
        Parameters:
        linkName - name of the link
        target - entity to link with
        Returns:
        true if target is not equal to old target
        See Also:
        addLink(String, Entity), addLink(String, EntityId), getLink(String), getLinks(String), getLinks(Collection), setLink(String, EntityId), deleteLink(String, Entity), deleteLink(String, EntityId), deleteLinks(String), getLinkNames()
